review_blob: Consistent.  Flavorful.  Kicks US/EU corporate beers right in the arse.  Say what you will, this is often times better than drinking  most commercial alternatives.  Dont fool yourself, this tastes the same in any UK pub.
Yuck!  Too much alcohol aroma and taste.  No distinct flavor to capture the palate.  Not memorable.  And  no need to repeat.  British beers tend to disappoint.

This is a stout with balls.  Big hairy balls. One of the finest microbrews ever allowed for mere mortals.  If only any other stout could match the perfection.  The multiple colors of this fine stout boggles the mind like vintage 60s LSD.  Only stout that Ive found that comes close to even teasing would be Rogue Shakespeare Stout.   Drink up and trip out.
Had this on tap at the brewery in Flagstaff.  Surprisingly full bodied with a rounded taste.
beer_name: Beaver Street R & R Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Great aroma belies the taste - which there seems to be very little of.  Disappointing.
This is a sweet black brew with a  frothy, tan foam.  It contains notes of coffee, and earthy, smoky woody taste.  This full  creamy bodied ale is highly recommeded.  Consistent.

When pregnant and wanting to celebrate/hang-out with drinkers - this beer gets huge thumbs up!  I tried every NA out there and this was the ONLY thing  that even partly made me feel as though I was enjoying an actual beer.  Kudos to the Guiness folks!
Ugh!  Had this when there was no other option.  Complete cat piss.  Dont waste your money or time.  Better off drinking water.

Had this on-tap at the brewery in Flagstaff.   Delicious.  Served with a lemon wedge - but I dont get into this.  Who wants lemon in their beer?  Enjoyed this beer above the others tried at the brewery.
Have always been a fan of the Belgian Ale.  This particular brew has a medium sweetness with a slightly bitter afternote.
Way too hoppy, which over-rode any character in the flavor.  Very disappointed considering the reputation.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged
